      • getJson

        public java.lang.String getJson()

      • getLastModified

        public java.lang.String getLastModified()
        Returns:
        The date and time the data returned was last updated. Used by clients in the `If-Modified-Since` request header.

      • getResponseCode

        public int getResponseCode()
        Returns:
        The HTTP response code given by the API. Value is 200 if the response is successful, 304 if data was not modified and the If-Modified-Since header is used, 401 if no TBA v3 API Key was provided, or it is not valid, or 404 if the URL or parameter(s) provided is invalid
